        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A five-minute bedtime tapping practice from Day 28 of a 30-day sleep programme. The night tap for Day 28 works with the vigilance that can persist even when the external situation is safe, the body scanning for a reason to tense up, unable to fully stand down. The reframe trains a new signal: stillness means protection, not danger.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
